-1 text-green-700\">Insurance document uploaded successfully</span>\r\n                    <button type=\"button\" onClick={removeInsuranceDocument} className=\"text-red-500 text-sm hover:text-red-700 font-medium\">Remove</button>\r\n                  </div>\r\n                )}\r\n              </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n            <div className=\"mb-6\">\r\n              <h2 className=\"font-semibold mb-4\">Pickup Information</h2>\r\n\r\n              <div className=\"mb-4\">\r\n                <button\r\n                  type=\"button\"\r\n                  onClick={() => {\r\n                    if (!navigator.geolocation) {\r\n                      alert('Geolocation is not supported by your browser');\r\n                      return;\r\n                    }\r\n\r\n                    navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition(\r\n                      (position) => {\r\n                        const { latitude, longitude } = position.coords;\r\n                        fetch(`https://photon.komoot.io/reverse?lat=${latitude}&lon=${longitude}`)\r\n                          .then((res) => res.json())\r\n                          .then((data) => {\r\n                            const address = data.features[0]?.properties?.display_name || 'Unknown location';\r\n                            handleChange({\r\n                              target: { name: 'pickupAddress', value: address },\r\n                            } as React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>);\r\n                          })\r\n                          .catch(() => alert('Could not fetch address from location'));\r\n                      },\r\n                      () => alert('Location access denied')\r\n                    );\r\n                  }}\r\n                  className=\"text-sm text-blue-600 hover:underline mb-3 flex items-center gap-1\"\r\n                >\r\n                  ≡ƒôì Use my current location\r\n                </button>\r\n\r\n                <AddressAutocomplete\r\n                  value={formData.pickupAddress}\r\n                  onChange={(newValue) =>\r\n                    handleChange({\r\n                      target: { name: 'pickupAddress', value: newValue },\r\n                    } as React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>)\r\n                  }\r\n                  onBlur={handleBlur}\r\n                  placeholder=\"Search or select address...\"\r\n                  error={errors.pickupAddress}\r\n                  touched={touched.pickupAddress}\r\n                />\r\n              </div>\r\n\r\n              <InputField\r\n                label=\"Regional Contact\"\r\n                name=\"regionalContact\"\r\n                type=\"tel\"\r\n                placeholder=\"e.g., 9445678210\"\r\n                value={formData.regionalContact}\r\n                onChange={handleChange}\r\n                onBlur={handleBlur}\r\n                error={errors.regionalContact}\r\n                touched={touched.regionalContact}\r\n              />\r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n            <div className=\"border-t pt-6 mb-6\">\r\n              <h2 className=\"font-semibold mb-4\">Legal Acknowledgement</h2>\r\n              <div className=\"bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md\">\r\n                <label className=\"flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer\">\r\n                  <input\r\n                    type=\"checkbox\"\r\n                    checked={legalAcknowledgement}\r\n                    onChange={(e) => setLegalAcknowledgement(e.target.checked)}\r\n                    className=\"mt-1 w-4 h-4 text-blue-600 border-gray-300 rounded focus:ring-blue-500\"\r\n                  />\r\n                  <span className=\"text-sm text-gray-700\">\r\n                    I confirm that I am the legal owner of this vehicle. I voluntarily provide my RC, insurance details, and document images to RentNRide for vehicle verification and rental purposes. I understand that these documents will be securely stored and used 